    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 7000 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - 7000 SERIES BUMPER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>7000 SERIES BUMPER</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Bumper Removal</title>
            <para>The 7000 Series Aerodynamic bumper is attached to the chassis bumper mounting brackets utilizing (4)
                four mounting bolts.
            </para>
            <para>Refer to Figure 12.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Beginning at the upper two bolts, loosen bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove both lower bumper bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Supporting the bumper, remove the two remaining upper bolts. Remove bumper.</para>
                <figure id="f0900712" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900712.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                             scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 12. Bumper Removal</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. FRONT BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. UPPER AND LOWER MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Bumper Install</title>
            <para>Beginning at the upper bolt hole of the steel bumper:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the bumper mounting holes with the mounting bracket holes.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert bolts in the upper holes, one driver side, one passenger side. Hand tighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the lower bumper mounting holes and insert lower bolts, and hand tighten.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Finish tightening the bumper bolts with socket to the torque requirement as designated
                    in the torque chart.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
